import React, { useEffect, useState } from 'react'; function SchemesExplorer() { const [state, setState] = useState('All'); const allSchemes = [ { name: 'PM-KISAN', summary: 'Direct income support to farmers.', state: 'All', url: 'https://pmkisan.gov.in/' }, { name: 'Soil Health Card', summary: 'Provides soil health cards to farmers.', state: 'All', url: 'https://soilhealth.dac.gov.in/' }, { name: 'KALIA', summary: 'Comprehensive assistance for cultivators in Odisha.', state: 'Odisha', url: 'https://kalia.odisha.gov.in/' }, { name: 'Rythu Bandhu', summary: 'Investment support for farmers in Telangana.', state: 'Telangana', url: 'https://treasury.telangana.gov.in/rythubandhu/' }, { name: 'Mukhya Mantri Krishi Ashirwad', summary: 'Direct benefit transfer scheme for Jharkhand farmers.', state: 'Jharkhand', url: 'https://mmkasy.jharkhand.gov.in/' }, { name: 'Krishi Yantra Subsidy', summary: 'Subsidy on farm machinery in Maharashtra.', state: 'Maharashtra', url: 'https://mahaagri.gov.in/Site/Home/Department_of_Agriculture,_Maharashtra_State,_India' } ]; const states = ['All', 'Odisha', 'Telangana', 'Jharkhand', 'Maharashtra']; const schemes = state === 'All' ? allSchemes : allSchemes.filter(s => s.state === state || s.state === 'All'); return (
